# The pebble TEST CA (minica) root — TEST MATERIAL ONLY, with a PUBLICLY-KNOWN private key.
#
# This is the root that signs pebble's OWN HTTPS endpoints (the ACME directory at :14000 and the
# management API at :15000); the rehearsal hands it to the plane as --acme-extra-root so the ACME client
# can reach the test directory over TLS, and to curl for the management-API fetch. It is shipped inside
# the pebble repository and image (test/certs/pebble.minica.pem) — its key is public, so NEVER trust this
# root outside this rehearsal.
#
# Note this is NOT the root pebble ISSUES certificates from: pebble mints a fresh issuing CA on every
# boot, and the rehearsal script fetches that one live from the management API (GET /roots/0).
#
# Extracted from the pinned image:
#   ghcr.io/letsencrypt/pebble@sha256:ddf230642b1a584f519f32e347de1b05a6e4c1f6c35c1863b33effeab5f78199
